      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The following reaction takes place in two steps, one of which is a cycloaddition while the other is a <i>reverse</i> cycloaddition. Identify the two pericyclic reactions, and show how they occur.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ1lhIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e440d6eec9d46b31ae88c9435ad503e0157ba391/OChem_30_EC_014.jpg\" alt=\"A five-carbon cyclic ester reacts with alkyne having two esters in heat to form a benzene ring bonded with two esters and carbon dioxide as the second product.\">",
